      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MILLSTEE (7) bumped into a good winner last start over 1000m at this track, but the late splits she ran in defeat were superb. Out in trip now and an inside barrier are both big ticks and she looks ready to go to another level now. Can get the job done this time around. DESERT DANCING (4) is another who steps up in trip today and she boasts a strong second-up record. The form out of her fresh run has been franked and she maps to get every chance from the barrier. Ticks plenty of boxes and she makes plenty of appeal with the fresh run under her belt. GIRLS DAY OUT (3) led and won 94 days ago and has been freshened since winning a trial recently in readiness for her return. She has the speed to roll forward from the barrier and she'll take catching. GO GO GROMMET (2) is on the quick turnaround after a 1.9L defeat on Wednesday. Can improve out in trip. MAI ALOHA (6) missed in a photo on Wednesday and is not to be discounted up in grade on the short turnaround.",
